  "instructions": [
    "Preheat the oven to 375 degrees Fahrenheit.",
    "Unroll the phyllo dough and cut it into squares.",
    "Brush the phyllo squares with butter or oil.",
    "Place a pandan leaf in the center of each square, followed by a spoonful of the malt syrup mixture.",
    "Roll the phyllo squares into tubes and place seam-side down in a baking dish.",
    "Cover the tubes with foil and bake for 25 minutes.",
    "Remove the foil and continue baking for an additional 10-15 minutes, or until the phyllo is golden brown.",
    "Allow the galaktoboureko to cool for 10 minutes before serving.",
    "Serve warm, garnished with additional pandan leaves and a drizzle of honey.",
    "Refrigerate any leftovers and serve chilled or at room temperature."
